# Text blocks

Text Blocks feature arrived in Java 15. For details, see [*JEP 378: Text Blocks*][1].

Enclose your material in a pair of triple QUOTATION MARK characters.


```java
String html = &quot;&quot;&quot;
              &lt;html&gt;
                  &lt;body&gt;
                      &lt;p&gt;Hello, world&lt;/p&gt;
                  &lt;/body&gt;
              &lt;/html&gt;
              &quot;&quot;&quot;;
```

Your [IDE][2] has likely been updated to be savvy in assisting you with editing text blocks. For example, [IntelliJ offers support][3].


